ogical changes that characterise the function and purpose of the western historiographical tradition in this formative period of its development.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aHistoriographyzEuropexHistoryyTo 1500. 0aRhetoric, Medieval. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aChristian historiography.  aMiddle Ages.  abiblical tradition.  achronographic tradition.  aclassical tradition.  adeliberative rhetoric.  adisposition.  aelocution.  aepideictic rhetoric.  ajudicial rhetoric.  amemoria.  anon-Christian historiography.  apronuntiatio.  atruth.  averisimilitude.  awestern Europe.1 aKempshall, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779898540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847798985423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847798985/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles